l enable post-secondary instructors to maximize their courses’ potential including undergraduate projects, graduate level co-teaching, pair and group co-teaching, co-taught single-subject courses, and innovative cross-curricular experiments. Contributors share their insights addressing key factors such as logistics, resources, administrative support, Ministry initiatives, and academic freedom. Jarvis and Kariuki have created an indispensable resource that provides the reader with an informed perspective on the realities of creating and sustaining rich co-teaching experiences at the university level.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aTeaching teams. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aAshworth, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerguson, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGame, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraham, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatt, Blaine E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaye, Roberta La, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIquette, Renée Val, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarvi, Daniel H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarvis, Daniel H. , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJarvis, Daniel H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKariuki, Mumbi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKariuki, Mumbi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLevenberg, Ilana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMetcalfe, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/